The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Bimal Khan, a 42-year-old resident of Bishnupur, died after being beaten up in his home, allegedly by three men who had borrowed money from him, on Sunday afternoon. Manmatha Das was arrested and one of his sons detained in connection with the incident. Dass other son is absconding. The three had borrowed Rs 30,000 from Khan.    Aparna Hazra, a 30-year-old homemaker, was allegedly strangled by her husband Dipankar in their Uluberia home on Sunday. Police claimed Dipankar, who was arrested, had confessed to the murder.     An unidentified man was killed when a vehicle knocked him down from behind on CR Avenue, near Girish Park, on Sunday afternoon. Police said the mishap occurred around 3.30pm when the man was crossing the road. He was declared dead at Calcutta Medical College and Hospital.    Thirty members of the Eastern Railway Workers Union were allegedly beaten up by a gang while they were holding a meeting near Naihati station on Sunday morning.                                                                                                                                               
